  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anastomotic leak after radical gastrectomy is a serious complication. Intraoperative leak
      testing was often used to assess the integrity of the anastomosis. However, the reliability,
      clinical benefits and safety of intraoperative leak testing are controversial. Our aim is to
      evaluate the effect and safety of intraoperative leak testing, and to compare the surgical
      complications of patients in intraoperative leak testing group with patients in
      non-intraoperative leak testing group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
